      "writtenOn": "2021-03-30T11:05:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This won\u0027t dedupe if the ScheduleBuild request is retried with a different batch containing the same requests, for example if the caller retries a subset of the builds handled in a previous request. Is that an issue for ResultDB? It would be nice if it could dedupe by individual requests in a batch.\n\nNot batching at all avoids this problem while simultaneously simplifying implementation, though the obvious trade-off is that it\u0027s inefficient.",
      "revId": "ae81b31b939260bb8b6d9983061b0f0fa1c4460e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d94df4c3_db0279d6",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/internal/resultdb/resultdb.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 91,
      "author": {
        "id": 1398165
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-30T19:14:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The ResultDB side will do the dedup by using the BatchCreateInvocationsRequest.RequestId. So if it\u0027s the whole batch retry, it can identify.\n\nBut if it\u0027s the partial retry where a batch contains a subset of already handled builds, I think the ResultDB won\u0027t dedup it and would create new invocations?@robertocn correct me if it\u0027s wrong. But I think this partial retry scenario should be handled in earlier ScheduleBuild flow before it reaches to this function, right?",
      "parentUuid": "7ee71ca8_ad383f2a",
      "revId": "ae81b31b939260bb8b6d9983061b0f0fa1c4460e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
